   "topic": "Consent in children: parental consent, the mature minor (Gillick), the best-interest / court override, and special procedures (Marion's case)",
   "subarea": "Theatre safety & consent",
   "trap": "- **Under-18 default**: parent/guardian consents in the child's best interests\n- **Mature minor (Gillick competence)**, approved in **Marion's case** (HCA):\n  - A child with sufficient understanding/intelligence to fully comprehend the proposed treatment **can consent themselves**\n  - Parental consent then not required\n  - Competence is **decision-specific** and rises with the gravity of the procedure\n- **OVERRIDE**: a court (**parens patriae / Family Court**) can override BOTH a parent's refusal AND a competent minor's **refusal** of life-saving treatment\n  - Classic scenario: Jehovah's Witness teen refusing transfusion for leukaemia/haemorrhage where refusal poses serious threat to life/health\n- **Special Medical Procedures** require **court/tribunal authorisation**:\n  - Neither parents nor a Gillick-competent child can authorise **non-therapeutic sterilisation** (Marion's case)\n  - Similar for irreversible/non-therapeutic procedures\n- Exam-catch asymmetry: a mature minor's **CONSENT** can stand alone; their **REFUSAL** of life-saving treatment is more readily overridden",
   "whatFirst": "- Assess **Gillick competence** for THIS specific decision\n  - Competent minor may consent\n- If **refusal of life-saving treatment** (minor or parent) → escalate urgently to **senior + hospital legal/court (parens patriae)**\n- If **sterilisation/non-therapeutic special procedure** → **Family Court/tribunal** authorisation required regardless of who consents",
   "discriminator": "- **Gillick CONSENT** vs **Gillick REFUSAL**:\n  - Consent by a competent minor: generally sufficient\n  - Refusal of life-saving treatment: courts **can override**\n- **Ordinary surgery**: parent or mature minor consents\n- **Special procedures** (e.g. sterilisation): **court only** — Marion's case",
