   "topic": "Factors impairing wound healing — the modifiable vs the killer ones (and the steroid/vitamin trap)",
   "subarea": "Wound healing & SSI",
   "trap": "**Local factors** impairing wound healing:\n- **Infection** — commonest cause of delay\n- **Ischaemia**/poor perfusion\n- **Foreign body**\n- Tension, oedema, irradiated tissue, haematoma\n\n**Systemic factors**:\n- **Diabetes** (esp. uncontrolled — target perioperative glucose)\n- **Smoking** (vasoconstriction + carboxyhaemoglobin — stop ideally several weeks pre-op)\n- **Malnutrition** (albumin/protein; vitamin C needed for collagen hydroxylation; zinc)\n- Age, obesity, chronic steroid/immunosuppression, chemo/radiotherapy, renal/hepatic failure, jaundice\n\nClassic MCQ trap:\n- **Chronic corticosteroids** impair healing\n- **Vitamin A** is the specific agent that partially reverses steroid-induced impairment\n  - Steroids stabilise lysosomes/blunt inflammation; Vit A counteracts this\n- **Vitamin C deficiency** (scurvy) impairs collagen cross-linking specifically",
   "whatFirst": "Optimise the **modifiable** before elective surgery:\n- **Glycaemic control**\n- **Smoking cessation**\n- **Nutrition/protein** optimisation\n- Treat **infection**\n- Relieve **pressure/tension**",
   "discriminator": "- **Vitamin C** = collagen synthesis (hydroxylation of proline/lysine)\n- **Vitamin A** = reverses steroid-impaired healing\n- **Zinc** = epithelialisation\n- **Steroids** = blunt inflammatory phase",
