   "subarea": "Wound healing & SSI",
   "trap": "Per eTG + ACSQHC Antimicrobial Stewardship Clinical Care Standard:\n- Prophylactic IV antibiotic given **WITHIN 60 MINUTES before incision** (ideally 15-30 min before knife-to-skin)\n- **Vancomycin** started **30-120 min before incision** because of slow infusion\n- Standard adult: **cefazolin 2 g IV** (child **30 mg/kg** up to 2 g)\n- **Re-dose intra-op** if procedure exceeds ~2x the drug half-life\n  - Cefazolin: re-dose **~every 4 hours** or with major blood loss (>1.5 L)\n- Prophylaxis must **NOT continue beyond 24 hours** (usually a single dose)\n- Maintain **normothermia (≥36°C)**\n- Perioperative glucose generally **<10 mmol/L**\n- Hair removal: **do NOT shave** with a razor — use **clippers** (or no removal) and only if hair interferes with surgery\n\nBig trap: **'continue prophylactic antibiotics for 3-5 days post-op'** — WRONG; single dose, max 24 h",
