   "trap": "SSI timing windows:\n- **Superficial incisional SSI**: within **30 days** of surgery (always 30 days)\n- **Deep incisional** and **Organ/Space SSI**: within **30 OR 90 days** depending on operative-procedure category\n  - 90-day window applies to defined procedures, many of them **implant operations** (joint prosthesis/hernia mesh/cardiac)\n  - Old blanket **'1 year for any implant'** window is superseded\n\nThree depths:\n- **Superficial incisional** — skin/subcutaneous only\n- **Deep incisional** — fascia and/or muscle\n- **Organ/Space** — any anatomy opened or manipulated (e.g. intra-abdominal abscess, joint space, mediastinum)\n\nTrap: conflating cellulitis-only with SSI — a **stitch abscess or isolated suture-site reaction is specifically excluded** from SSI",
