   "subarea": "Open disclosure & M&M",
   "trap": "- **Sentinel events** = defined national subset of adverse events that are **wholly preventable** and cause serious harm/death\n- They are **always SAC 1**, **mandatorily reported**, and trigger **RCA + formal open disclosure**\n- Current list (**version 2**): agreed by Health Ministers **December 2018**, commenced **1 July 2019**; **10 categories** (specifications updated **May 2025**)\n- Classic surgical gotchas: the **'wrong-wrong-wrong + retained + ABO' cluster** all sit here\n- MCQs love: which scenario **IS a listed sentinel event** vs merely a serious complication\n  - A recognised, consented complication of surgery is **NOT** a sentinel event\n  - **Wrong-site surgery IS**",
   "source": "Australian Sentinel Events List version 2 Specifications, ACSQHC (commenced 1 July 2019; specifications updated May 2025)",
   "discriminator": "- **Sentinel event** = on the defined list, wholly preventable, never-event style\n- A **serious but recognised/consented complication** (e.g. anastomotic leak, expected bleeding) = adverse event but **NOT** a sentinel event\n- **Wrong patient/site/procedure, retained object, ABO-incompatible transfusion** = sentinel\n- Use the **WHO checklist / surgical time-out** as the prevention link for the surgical four",
   "whatFirst": "- Identify it as a sentinel event\n- Ensure **patient safety**\n- **Mandatory external notification** per jurisdiction\n- **Secure evidence** (e.g. retained item, blood bag)\n- Commence **formal open disclosure**\n- Initiate **RCA**\n- Do **NOT delay patient disclosure** pending the RCA",
   "redFlags": "- Any of the following → **mandatory reporting + RCA**:\n  - **Wrong site, wrong patient, wrong procedure**\n  - **Retained foreign object**\n  - **ABO-incompatible haemolytic transfusion**\n  - In-patient **suicide** (acute psychiatric)\n  - Serious **medication error**\n  - **Restraint-related** serious harm\n  - Infant/child discharge to **unauthorised person**\n  - **Mis-placed naso/oro-gastric tube** causing serious harm",
   "mcqTrap": "- 'A patient develops an anastomotic leak after consented bowel resection — this is a sentinel event' — **WRONG**\n  - A recognised complication is **not on the sentinel list**\n  - Trap pairs a genuinely severe-but-expected complication with the 'sentinel' label\n  - Only **listed, wholly-preventable events** qualify",
   "viva": "- Examiner: 'Name **three surgical sentinel events** and how the WHO checklist prevents them'\n  - **Wrong-site/patient/procedure + retained object**\n  - Prevented by **sign-in/time-out/sign-out**, site marking, swab/instrument counts\n  - Discriminator: candidate separates **'sentinel/never event'** from **'recognised complication'**",
   "mnemonic": "Surgical sentinel core = ‘4 W’s + ABO’: Wrong site, Wrong patient, Wrong procedure, retained Widget (foreign object), ABO-incompatible transfusion.",
